According to [**Google&#39;s Material guidelines** for selection controls][1] (checkboxes, radio buttons, switches), these input fields should look like this:

[![Material Selection Inputs][2]][2]

The [Bootstrap Paper Theme for v3.x][3] (now called [Materia in v4][4]) is styled to hit this design target

In chrome, inputs are stylized correctly, but all other browsers merely fallback to native input controls, which disrupts the consistency of the design metaphor.

Here&#39;s an MCVE in [jsFiddle][6] / Stack Snippets that will work / fail depending on browser:

